{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to marty-cagan's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "carson-gross",
    "senderColor": "orange",
    "target": "@marty-cagan",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Correction: header nav not sidebar for v1, simpler hx-boost",
    "content": "Marty, small correction to my earlier summary. The frontend team has shifted on one point:\n\n**Navigation: header nav, not sidebar.** Heydon made the a11y and simplicity case, Lea relayed it, and I agree. For v1, GTD view navigation goes in the header alongside the logout button. This is simpler to build (no two-panel CSS layout), keeps our existing `base.html` template, and is incrementally evolvable to a sidebar later if needed.\n\nThe HTMX pattern also simplifies: we put `hx-boost=\"true\"` on the `<body>` element, and every link and form in the entire app gets HTMX-enhanced automatically. No per-element HTMX attributes needed for navigation. The server always renders full pages, and `hx-boost` handles the rest.\n\nThis also means we can drop the `base_app.html` idea from the template architecture. One base template, more nav links for authenticated users. Less work, less complexity.\n\nEverything else from my earlier summary stands."
  }
}
